The report on a controversial shacks project in Limpopo is yet to be released. The housing department in Talana, Tzaneen came under fire for its cost and shoddy workmanship. Manqoba Mchunu has been following this story. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A report into the structural quality of a multimillion-rand housing project in Limpopo has been delayed. This is because the Human Settlements Department has missed its own deadline. READ: Another shoddy multi-million rand shack project in Limpopo More than 40 structures were built in Talana in Tzaneen at a cost of R2-million. A similar project in Burgersfort cost R17-million but has now been halted after concerns were raised about it as well. Residents in the area have allegedly refused to occupy the units.